The paper deals with visual reasoning and memory in artificial intelligence, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The proposed deep learning architecture also involves training and learning, which are relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions natural language processing (cs.CL) in the context of visual question answering datasets.
